The paper discusses statistical relational learning (SRL) and its application to community structure analysis in social networks. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with social networks (cs.SOC) and databases (cs.DB) as it proposes a model for multi-relational networks. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of latent feature vectors, which is a common topic in the sub-category of social influence (cs.SI).
